# base64 round-trip

R.3.2 wires `base64Encode(s)` and `base64Decode(s)` to the
`base64 = "0.22"` crate (pulled into `Cargo.toml` only when at
least one of the two intrinsics is reached).

```scalascript
@main def run(): Unit =
  val msg: String = "hello rust"
  val enc: String = base64Encode(msg)
  val dec: String = base64Decode(enc)
  println(dec == msg)
```

Build and run:

```bash
ssc build-rust base64-roundtrip.ssc
./base64-roundtrip            # → true
```
